##Wuhan Community Worker: I am in the crack, responsible for getting scolded and report | story FM

Story

Features, welcome to the story FM. Here, we tell your story with your voice. Every Monday, Wednesday and Friday, all platforms are updated simultaneously.

Click on the picture above to jump to the "story FM" applet and listen to the real person. Remember to add "my little program" , one-click to listen to the whole story Yo!

During the outbreak, story FM interviewed doctors in Wuhan, diagnosed patients in a shelter hospital, and cancer patients in Wuhan... We tried to understand the situation at the heart of the epidemic through the stories of various groups in Wuhan.

The siege of Wuhan, according to Reuters, is the first in modern history to shut down a major city of 11 million people. Such a move would require an infinite number of tiny cogs to work together. The jobs that directly relate to Wuhan residents are those of community workers.

Today we call on a Wuhan community worker to speak about his experiences.

-1-

Go in the opposite direction

I was on duty on the third and fourth day of the Lunar New Year. I thought I could rest for three days after duty.

Which know I come home on the fourth night, secretary in the group notice: Fifth Day all staff on duty. As soon as I saw the news, I began to think ill of a way out.

Who can really go against the grain like everyone says? I'm not that noble. I'm really scared. But I had no choice. I had to go.

In the past, when I was on duty for the New Year, the community arranged for one person to be on duty for one day. After the closure of the city, the situation is more serious, so two people on duty. It's no exaggeration to say that we haven't been disconnected since we were on duty. There are also many people in the wechat group said that the phone simply can not get in, in fact, too many people are calling us.

A lot of people call the community if they have a mild case, and we recommend that they stay home for a few days. There are also people who come directly to the community, so one of us will answer the phone, and one of us will take care of the people who come to the community.

■ Community Workers Answer the phone photo / Xinhua News Agency

At that time, the number of patients continued to increase, and over the course of a few days, we registered more than 100 patients with fever. Other communities may have only a dozen or thirty. Compared to them, we have too many fever patients here. My colleagues and I know that many of the hospital staff who live on our side are very scared.

There was a lot of buzz around that time. Family members said that SARS patients even if cured, but also to take long-term medicine. It could be the same thing with this disease.

They're worried that if I go to work in my current protective state, what if I get it? My mom would get up in the morning, and she would sit in front of the house, and she wouldn't let me out. I can only get out when she goes back to bed. After about two or three times, she knew she couldn't stop me. She knew she couldn't control me.

I'll admit I'm one of those little people, but I've seen too many stranded families who wouldn't know who to call if I stopped working.

-2-

Screening patients for risk and doubt

Our office has issued two kinds of protective clothing. One is the white one-piece suit, which is a small number, and we only got ten in our community, and I've never worn one.

A more plentiful supply is another yellow suit. When you put it on, you're exposed below the knee, and it doesn't cover the whole body. The fabric is also thin, with small holes can be breathable, can not play the role of protection. That's what we wear when we're canvassing.

■ yellow protective clothing provided by storyteller

I'm in charge of the whole neighborhood, and I need to canvass a total of 1,300 homes with the sinking party cadre. The main contents of the investigation are: How many people live in the home, whether it is the owner / tenant, whether there is a fever situation / purchase of medicine and vegetables demand / personalized demand. The main purpose of screening is to identify potential cases.

We'll put a list of families with patients, close contacts, or suspected cases, and when we get to the floor of his house, we'll keep an eye out, stay as far away from his house as possible, and keep quiet, and keep that mask on a tight seal. But we're still wearing the same yellow suit.

At the time of screening, it is possible to encounter patients who do not develop symptoms within 14 days, which should be a potential risk.

I'm more concerned about the way we screen people with fevers. For example, if there are three people in a family, one of them has a fever, but it is only a slight fever, so the family does not want to send him to the hospital. How many people are there in your family? They could have said there were two of them, so the sweep would have put them down as two of them. If they say there are three people in the house, no one has a fever. The investigators could only record that no one had a fever.

I think such a way is useless, because only the police station will know how many people there are in each family. Not to mention there may be residents directly do not open the door, do not make a sound, sitting at home waiting for us to leave.

My mother once asked me: Do you check this useful? He wouldn't even come through the door. But the problem is that when people don't let us in, we don't let ourselves in. I've discussed it with my colleagues, and we all agree that the current sweep is a fool's errand.

Of course, this is only for patients with fever, not for other screening content. For example, the residents will tell us what they want to buy, what they need.

Staff members list of items required for resident registration

-3-

The community has no rights

Not long after the shutdown, the owner's mother herself estimated that there was a 99 percent chance of new coronary pneumonia, but the nucleic acid test results had not been available at the time.

After the closure of the city, the car can not out of the community, the owner will call the community said want to send her mother to see a doctor, to the community car. But at the time, the community sent cars can only be used to protect people's livelihood, can not be used to send suspected or fever patients. Then I heard his mom passed out at home, and he called 120. But 120 was too busy, with 500 patients waiting in line.

Then he called 110 and asked to have his mother carried to their car and taken to the hospital. 110 says they can't lift without protection.

Finally, he called our community and asked them to carry it. At that time, our only protective measures are masks and that can only be used as psychological comfort protective clothing, we also have no way to lift.

He said, okay, you wait for me to come to the community right away! And went straight to our neighborhood. He was a confidant, but he didn't wear a mask. As soon as he came in, he kicked out the two tables in front of him and kept cursing at us. All of us were afraid to look him in the face, so we walked away or out the back door. It was a sight I'll never forget.

The next day, his mother was diagnosed. In the evening, he came again. The neighborhood was a 24-hour shift, and he was afraid to open the door when his co-worker was alone.

To be honest, I've seen too much of this already. Back then, everyone thought the community could connect him directly to the hospital, to the hospital, to the car. Everyone felt that the community had a right to help him with any medical care.

But really, all the community can do is upload and distribute. We keep people waiting because we're told to. All we can do is register.

Back then, people often asked for help on Weibo, saying that the community ignored them, but we didn't. As long as it's what the residents report to the community, we're reporting it, just going through the normal process, waiting in line.

I've also seen people refuse to go to a hospital after getting them in touch.

One patient, a cancer patient, had gone to the hospital, and the hospital recommended that he be hospitalized immediately, asking him to get help from the community to contact the hospital where he could be hospitalized. We'll report him as a non-crown patient in critical condition, get him to a hospital. He asked to go only to hospitals where there were no new patients.

Then we got in touch with a hospital that had previously been treating new patients. After all the new coronary patients were shunted out, the hospital now specializes in treating non-febrile patients. But the patient said No. I've had two cases like this.

Community volunteers check residents'body temperature

-4-

Cute volunteer

The completion of the Shelter Hospital, so many need to be treated, suspected patients have a place to go, and the community home isolation of people are also sharply reduced. It's not so scary anymore.

I've got about 20 volunteers, all recruited on one platform. They were given only 20 suits, enough for these people to last a day. They wear it once a day, disinfect it with alcohol, and wear it again the next day. I myself wear only a mask at work and only wear protective clothing when I go to the door. I really want to save the suits for them.

One day, I was talking to a colleague on the way home from work. I asked three colleagues: If you didn't do this job, would you come out and volunteer? They all said they would stay at home and were afraid to volunteer. Later, I asked myself this question, I do not seem to choose to be a volunteer.

One of the volunteers was a young girl, and I was struck by the last thing I said to her the night before last. It's all about the people, she said. She's only 20 years old, and I could never say that when I was 20. I think the volunteers are a very respectable and lovely group of people.

Photo of demand group on Wechat / China News Service

-5-

Be Understood

When work is relatively easy, there is constant friction between residents and communities.

Something happened today. One owner called the community and said his daughter's online classes needed to be printed and he couldn't buy a printer. He sent me a PDF, which I had been working on for WORD  , but which I hadn't been able to format for a while because of the paper. At this time, a batch of vegetables just arrived, I need to tow, I told him something to busy, he can come directly to our community to print.

When I finished things, I saw him send Wechat scold me, the general idea is: You this eye make very big AH, first said to help me play, and now can not play out... similar words.

Every time I think about where I am right now, I feel sorry for myself. In a city like Wuhan, I get 2,364 yuan a month, and the definition of community is like a folk autonomous organization, which we don't have. Our health insurance, social security, plus the provident fund is a total of more than 570.

Sometimes I see news on the Internet about giving 10 points to the college entrance examination and high school entrance examination for the children of the first-line medical workers; all the scenic spots in Hubei Province are open to them free of charge for five years. Yesterday I saw the news that the medical staff can go home to rest, six days of rotation. Why didn't anyone see the community workers? Why is it that only health care workers are on the front line, and not our community workers?

I admit that they are more at risk than we are, but why does no one notice how the community workers live each day? I'm not trying to compete with angels, I'm just saying, why is it so different?

Image of community workers spreading knowledge of the epidemic / China News Service

One time when I was delivering food to an empty Nester, she grabbed me and insisted on giving me money. I told her it was free. She saluted me before I got on the elevator.

When I got in the elevator, I was in there crying. I don't know if it's because I'm pathetic or because they're pathetic. Maybe that's what it feels like when a poor person meets a poor person.

At that moment, I feel that all the previous grievances are forgivable. Even if all the people in the world are bad, if only one person is nice to me, and one person understands me, or understands my job, I can accept all the injustices that have happened before.

——————

So far today, Wuhan has been closed for 42 days, and all parts of the country have been under strict control for more than 40 days. This is a great test for the community workers, but also for all residents test.

In the face of an epidemic, each of us will encounter problems that others will not be aware of, and each of us will be eager for more listening and compassion. I hope that both sides can have a more understanding, so that the epidemic prevention work smoothly, but also let our community become warmer.
